div.p:
In accordance with your request,On November 30, Kissinger notified Rogers and Secretary of Transportation Volpe that the President wanted an “immediate investigation of the circumstances surrounding the alleged defection of the Soviet seaman to the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Vigilant.” Kissinger added that the two agencies should report their findings by the close of business on December 2. (Ibid.) reports have been submitted to you on this incident by Acting Secretary of State Irwin (Tab B) and Secretary of Transportation Volpe (Tab C).Both memoranda dated December 2; attached but not printed. Both reports agree generally (but diverge on specifics) that the investigations revealed the following two problems were immediately involved in this case:
—the Coast Guard unit involved was not adequately informed of the standing instructions and procedures for dealing with potential defectors;
—there was inadequate communication between the State Department and the Coast Guard.
